section.para:
      The GêBR interface is intentionally simple. It is organized in tabs:


	  Projects and Lines: for creating and manipulating
	  Projects and Lines;


	  Flows: for creating and executing Flows;


	  Flow Editor: for editing and executing a Flow;


	  Job Control: for inspecting the results.

GêBR also has additional resources in menu bar, on the top of
the window.


    Actions


        Preferences: User preferences;


        Connections Assistant: Step-by-step
        guided setup of the main connections performed by GêBR;


        Maestro/Servers: Configuration of
        Maestro, Servers and Groups of servers;


        Quit: quit GêBR.




    Help 


        Help: GêBR's documentation;


        Examples: examples of seismic processing;


        About: GêBR's version, license and
        staff information.
